songs.title: Havana (SummerBash 2017 Version)
songs.lyrics:
[Chorus]
Havana, ooh na-na
Half of my heart is in Havana, ooh-na-na
He took me back to East Atlanta, na-na-na
Oh, but my heart is in Havana
My heart is in Havana
Havana, ooh na-na

[Verse 1]
He didn't walk up with that "how you doin'?"
(When he came in the room)
He said there’s a lot of girls I can do with
(But I can't without you)
I knew him forever in a minute
(That summer night in June)
And papa says he got malo in him
I didn't listen

[Pre-Chorus]
I know he's the spot (hey)
We're running out of moonlight (hey)
People say that he is hot
So here's your ticket, girl, it's a shot
And I can't make decisions with the stress
Should I say yes? (uh-huh)

[Chorus]
Havana, ooh na-na
Half of my heart is in Havana, ooh-na-na
He took me back to East Atlanta, na-na-na
Oh, but my heart is in Havana
My heart is in Havana
Havana, ooh na-na

[Instrumental bridge: Pharrell]
Uh-huh
Hey

[Outro]
Havana, ooh-na-na
Da, da, da, da, da, da, da, yeah
Havana, ooh-na-na
Half of my heart is in Havana
My heart is in Havana
Havana, ooh-na-na
